12 Years after the pivotal release for Call of Duty Black Ops 2... the modern world looks a whole lot closer to that version of reality than anyone would have ever expected. 

From a rise in military automation, to quantum computing, and international trade wars... Treyarch predicted it all right down to the year... with a timeless video game that feels increasingly accurate with each passing month of the year. 

Obviously there are significant portions that don't match, but the mark of good Sci-Fi is plausibility, and Black Ops 2 is far more than just plausible. In a sense, it almost feels likely.
